reviews.headline: Smooth, affordable eyeliner with nice pigment, though it can
reviews.comments: The e.l.f. Smoky Kohl Eyeliner has smooth application and great pigmentation for the price. It glides on easily without tugging and blends well for a smoky look. The color payoff lasts a few hours but may smudge slightly by the end of the day. Overall, it's affordable, beginner-friendly, and good value for money.

reviews.headline: It's a MUST for fall
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I'm obsessed with this eyelinerâ€”it's smooth, pigmented, and the perfect shade for fall. It works beautifully as a classic eyeliner but also doubles as a lip liner. I've been pairing it with the e.l.f. Lip Reviver Gloss for a chic, versatile look. Definitely a must-have in my makeup bag this season and you can't beat it for the price

reviews.headline: Specialized product, could be what you're looking for!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This liner is great for a smudged out liner look, however it has a tendency to rub away VERY easily. I achieved the look in the photo with just the pencil liner & a smudging brush, I had to keep going back over the liner I had applied because it kept disappearing. This definitely isn't for waterline application, no matter how well I dried my waterline this just wouldn't stick.

reviews.headline: So sharp and creamy
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This eyeliner is so sharp and dark! It's very creamy and easy to use. I just swipe it on and there's no need to reapply. I'm very happy with this. I think it's a great value for the money and the packaging is very simple.

reviews.headline: Love the depth of color
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I like the smooth application of the pen. Doesn't bother my sensitive eyes which is a plus. I love the dark black color. Stays on well so more difficult to remove. Packing easy to read.

reviews.headline: Switched from mechanical
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I usually don't use pencil and prefer the mechanical, but I liked this one a LOT! Goes on so easy and just like the mechanical and the color is perfect!! I've been wearing brown the past 3 years and this is perfect for lighter hair and darker hair girlies! This does easily smudge if you want that smudge look and it comes off easy without any hassle! I like it and I've added elf's pencil to my everyday lineup

reviews.headline: Love

reviews.headline: Smoky

It definitely has the pencil eyeliner look and does smudge a little and can create the smoky appearance. I am more of a liquid eyeliner girl, but this is definitely a staple to have in your beauty collection.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Thank you Elf for choosing to give me a free product in return for an honest review. 

I received the Vintage Denim color which is a deep blue, almost black. After doing a color swatch, this is a very cool blue. Before blending it could be seen as black and id like to note it needed very little pressure to be applied very opaque. This product is very forgiving and allows you to blend it even a while after application. I have a light olive complexion and this color is beautiful for those who want to try a blue eyeliner but not ready to yet commit to a bright and eccentric look.
faceoff_positive.headline: So creamy!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I received this product for free in exchange for my review. 

I love elf products and use many of them! However, this one fell short for me. While the eyeliner does go on relatively smooth, I hate that it's a pencil and doesn't come with a sharpener. We've come a long way in the beauty world and it felt like this didn't get the memo. It's also not very long lasting, which is a major bummer for me.
faceoff_negative.headline: Decent enough
